			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It's much simpler to just treat triangle frequencies above 20kHz as silent (or more correctly, as 50% amplitude, i.e. send 7.5 to the DAC). With the low 3 bits of $400B set to 0, these low values for $400A yield the following frequencies:
<br />
<br />0 55.9 kHz
<br />1 28.0 kHz
<br />2 18.6 kHz
<br />3 14.0 kHz
<br />...
<br />
<br />You could treat the first two or three entries as being inaudible, depending on how good your hearing is.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

